limits), or <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for the sum of at least the <strong>correct</strong> first three terms of the sequence.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>12</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>855</mn><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>855</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>371</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p>finding <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>24</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3539</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>…</mo></math> or attempt to find the sum between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>13</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>24</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>24</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3539</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>…</mo></math> <strong>or</strong> sigma notation that includes correct limits and their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> formula <strong>or</strong> a substituted geometric series formula that includes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>125</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>537</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math> <strong>or</strong> a list of terms that includes at least the&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>13</mn><mi>th</mi></msup></math> term and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>24</mn><mi>th</mi></msup></math> term.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3539</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>855</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>371</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mn>13</mn><mn>24</mn></munderover><mfenced><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>S</mi><mrow><mn>13</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>to</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>125</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>537</mn><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>12</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>125</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>537</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>358</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>172</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Accept a calculation using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>13</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>125</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>126</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2680</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2684</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2684</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2685</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>13</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>125</mn></math>, the sum is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2673</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>13</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>126</mn></math>, the sum is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2694</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p></div>","meta":{"questionId":"35019321","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.3b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use this model to find the total number of cars that will be sold in the year 2025. 2026.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}